---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config.ts';
---

<Base title={SITE.title} description={SITE.description}>
  <Nav />
  <main id="main">
    <Hero />

    <Section id="problem" heading="The problem">
      <p>
        Humanoids, cobots, and autonomous robots are moving out of industrial
        cages and into shared spaces around people. Their behavior is
        increasingly driven by AI, rather than by hand-coded logic.
      </p>
      <p>
        As these robots take on continuously improving artificial brains, they
        become more capable but less predictable in what they do. Without ways
        to constrain what robots can do, risk is hard to bound, accountability
        is difficult to establish, and deployment of AI-driven robots around
        people slows. Addressing this problem requires a layer between the
        AI's decisions and the robot's motion.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section id="what-we-do" heading="What we do" variant="tinted">
      <p>
        We are building runtime safety software for AI-driven robots. The
        software is the execution boundary between the brain and the body,
        where decisions become motion. At that boundary, the software
        measures, records, and bounds what the robot does, regardless of
        what the AI decides or how it evolves.
      </p>
      <div class="my-6 md:my-8 flex justify-center">
        <svg
          role="img"
          aria-label="Architecture: Decision feeds MindMotion's Software which controls Motion"
          viewBox="0 0 600 160"
          class="w-full max-w-[720px] h-auto text-accent"
        >
          <title>Decision &rarr; MindMotion&rsquo;s Software &rarr; Motion</title>

          <rect x="20" y="45" width="120" height="70" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" />
          <text x="80" y="80" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" font-family="Inter, system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="18" font-weight="600" fill="currentColor">DECISION</text>

          <line x1="145" y1="80" x2="200" y2="80" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" />
          <polygon points="200,73 213,80 200,87" fill="currentColor" />

          <rect x="220" y="45" width="220" height="70" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" />
          <text x="330" y="80" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" font-family="Inter, system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="18" font-weight="600" fill="currentColor">MindMotion&rsquo;s Software</text>

          <line x1="445" y1="80" x2="500" y2="80" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" />
          <polygon points="500,73 513,80 500,87" fill="currentColor" />

          <rect x="520" y="45" width="70" height="70" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" />
          <text x="555" y="80" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" font-family="Inter, system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="18" font-weight="600" fill="currentColor">MOTION</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </Section>

    <Section id="why-now" heading="Why now">
      <p>
        AI-driven robots are challenging to deploy safely around people at
        scale. Safety at scale requires an execution boundary that separates
        decision-making from execution.
      </p>
      <p>
        Aviation, automotive, and computing each reached a moment when
        execution had to be separated from decision-making. Robotics is at
        the same moment.
      </p>
    </Section>

    {/* Insights preview section wired in Step 4 once content collection exists. */}
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
